title: Winter (Photography Art Ebook).pdf
description:
McClelland and Stewart / 1974 / pdf / English / 15.7 MB

Late one night I was at the front window of my Toronto home. It snowed. For hours
it had been snowing, the first heavy fall coming in the middle of December. Heavy
flakes drifting across the overhanging comer street light masked the familiar fences
and trees. Beside me, his paws up on the window sill while he waited to go out on
his run to the comer, was our big white standard poodle, who kept turning his head
to me as if he couldn't figure out what was happening to his territory. He was a pup.
just six months old. He had never seen snow. But for me it was the beginning of
another white winter...
